5 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF THE KENTUCKY RULES OF
6 EVIDENCE IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
7 (a) Except as provided in subdivision (b) of this rule, a statement made by a child in
8 the course of a custodial interrogation that did not comply with applicable
9 statutes is not admissible against the child in any civil, criminal, or juvenile
10 proceeding.
11 (b) Evidence excluded in subdivision (a) of this rule is admissible if otherwise
12 admissible under these rules, and offered by the plaintiff in an action for
13 damages arising from the interrogation.
